## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This test plan defines the testing strategy, scope, schedule, and resources for the **Injector** module (KSA-3) of the Kiro SDLC Agent VS Code extension. The Injector is responsible for copying bundled resource files from the extension’s installation directory into the user’s workspace, supporting full injection, selective injection, recursive copy with exclusions, filtered copy, and status checking.

### 1.2 Test Objectives

* Verify all five functional features (injectAll, injectSelective, copyDirRecursive, copyFiltered, checkStatus) work per FSD specifications
* Validate all 17 business rules (BR-1 through BR-17) are correctly enforced
* Ensure directory exclusion logic is case-sensitive and applies at any depth
* Verify cross-platform path handling (Windows, macOS, Linux)
* Confirm error handling produces correct user-facing messages per FSD Section 9
* Validate non-functional requirements (performance ≤ 5s, async I/O, reliability)

