## 2. Test Strategy

### 2.1 Test Levels

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Level | Scope | Automation | Tools |
| PBT | Correctness properties for exclusion logic, filter matching, path handling | Automated | vitest + fast-check |
| UT | Unit tests for individual functions (copyDirRecursive, copyFiltered, checkStatus) | Automated | vitest + mock-fs |
| IT | Integration tests with real file system operations | Automated | vitest + tmp directories |
| E2E-API | N/A (no REST API — VS Code extension module) | N/A | N/A |
| E2E-UI | VS Code extension command execution via test harness | Automated | @vscode/test-electron |
| SIT | Manual exploratory testing in VS Code | Manual | VS Code + manual |

### 2.2 Test Types

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Type | Description | Applicable |
| Functional Testing | Verify features work per FSD use cases (UC-1 to UC-5) | Yes |
| Regression Testing | Ensure existing extension features are not broken | Yes |
| Performance Testing | Verify copy completes within 5 seconds for < 500 files | Yes |
| Security Testing | Verify no path traversal, permission handling | Yes |
| Compatibility Testing | Verify cross-platform (Windows, macOS, Linux) | Yes |
| Usability Testing | Verify QuickPick UI behavior | Yes |

### 2.3 Test Approach

* **Risk-based prioritization**: High-priority tests cover core copy logic and exclusion rules (most likely to have defects)
* **Property-based testing**: Use random inputs to verify exclusion and filter invariants hold for any valid input
* **Mock file system**: Unit tests use mock-fs to simulate directory structures without real I/O
* **Real file system**: Integration tests create temporary directories to verify actual copy behavior
* **VS Code test harness**: E2E-UI tests use @vscode/test-electron to run commands in a real VS Code instance

