## 4. Test Environment

### 4.1 Environment Requirements

|  |  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Environment | Platform | Node.js | VS Code | Purpose |
| Dev/UT | Windows 11 | 18.x+ | 1.85+ | Unit + Integration tests |
| CI | Linux (GitHub Actions) | 18.x+ | Latest | Automated test pipeline |
| SIT | Windows 11 / macOS 14 / Ubuntu 22.04 | 18.x+ | 1.85+ | Manual cross-platform testing |

### 4.2 Test Data Requirements

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Data Type | Description | Source | Preparation |
| Extension resources | Mock directory structure with agents, steering, hooks, templates, scripts | Test fixtures | Create in test setup |
| Workspace directory | Empty temp directory simulating workspace | OS temp | Create per test |
| Nested directories | Deep directory tree with excluded dirs at various depths | Test fixtures | Create in test setup |
| Large file set | 500+ files for performance testing | Generated | Script to create dummy files |

### 4.3 External Dependencies

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| System | Dependency | Mock/Stub Available |
| VS Code API | vscode.window.showQuickPick, vscode.workspace | Yes — @vscode/test-electron provides real API |
| Node.js fs | File system operations | Yes — mock-fs for UT, real fs for IT |
| OS file system | Cross-platform path resolution | Yes — test on all 3 platforms in CI |

