## 7. Risk & Mitigation

|  |  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| # | Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| 1 | Cross-platform path differences cause failures | High | Medium | Test on all 3 OS in CI; use path.join() consistently |
| 2 | Mock-fs doesn’t accurately simulate real fs behavior | Medium | Low | Supplement with real-fs integration tests |
| 3 | VS Code test harness instability | Medium | Medium | Pin @vscode/test-electron version; retry flaky tests |
| 4 | Large directory trees cause timeout in tests | Low | Low | Set generous timeout; use smaller fixtures for UT |
| 5 | Permission issues differ across OS | Medium | Medium | Test with restricted permissions on each platform |

## 8. Defect Management

### 8.1 Severity Levels

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Severity | Definition | Example |
| Critical | Core copy logic broken, data loss | Files silently not copied; workspace corrupted |
| Major | Feature not working, workaround exists | Exclusion list not applied at nested depth |
| Minor | UI issue, cosmetic defect | QuickPick description text incorrect |
| Trivial | Typo, minor alignment issue | Log message typo |

### 8.2 Priority Levels

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Priority | Definition | SLA (Fix Time) |
| P1 | Must fix immediately | 4 hours |
| P2 | Must fix before release | 1 business day |
| P3 | Should fix if time permits | 3 business days |
| P4 | Nice to fix, can defer | Next release |

### 8.3 Defect Lifecycle

New → Open → In Progress → Fixed → Ready for Retest → Verified → Closed
 → Reopened → In Progress

